The paper discusses the use of reinforcement learning algorithms in healthcare, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). It also touches on the evaluation of these algorithms, which could fall under the categories of computational engineering (cs.CE) and cybernetics (cs.CY). Finally, the paper emphasizes the importance of considering the clinical implications of these algorithms, which could fall under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
